01:00:26.900 --> 01:00:29.670
I said "well, you have a company that has
a lot of online business.

01:00:29.670 --> 01:00:30.670
You have a lot of stores."

01:00:30.670 --> 01:00:37.560
And he said, "yeah, but when I want to talk
to my manager, I go in and see him or I call

01:00:37.560 --> 01:00:39.580
him on a regular phone.

01:00:39.580 --> 01:00:41.320
But they don't need me pestering him.

01:00:41.320 --> 01:00:42.610
I don't need one of those things.

01:00:42.610 --> 01:00:45.330
I don't need for people to know where I am
all the time.

01:00:45.330 --> 01:00:46.750
I don't want to be a part of that."

01:00:46.750 --> 01:00:50.070
Then he went into -- he said to the audience.

01:00:50.070 --> 01:00:51.500
We were given these hands as tools.

01:00:51.500 --> 01:00:57.461
He said, "I started my business, in effect,
as a teenager fixing old cars.

01:00:57.461 --> 01:01:04.970
1938 cars taking apart, building them back
again; rappelling off cliffs to do falconry.

01:01:04.970 --> 01:01:11.220
My hands allowed me to do that and I strengthened
my legs and I learned how to climb vertically.

01:01:11.220 --> 01:01:17.840
I was in a ice cave for ten days in Monte
Fitz Roy in Chile.

01:01:17.840 --> 01:01:20.250
And I had a lot of time to think.

01:01:20.250 --> 01:01:22.359
Because I had no other devices to distract
me.

01:01:22.359 --> 01:01:25.260
That's where I got the idea for the company
that I now run.

01:01:25.260 --> 01:01:29.830
I needed better clothing that would last."

01:01:29.830 --> 01:01:38.140
Then I said to him, "but Yvan, in your passion,
climbing, cyber technology has now moved in.

01:01:38.140 --> 01:01:43.150
People are now taking their laptops with them
when they go to Himalayas or when they go

01:01:43.150 --> 01:01:44.150
to climb somewhere."

01:01:44.150 --> 01:01:47.490
You could just see the energy drain out of
him.

01:01:47.490 --> 01:01:53.130
And he said, "Yeah, there are probably some
of you in this room who have done this.

01:01:53.130 --> 01:01:57.970
You've hired an outfitter for 50,000 dollars
in the Himalayas.

01:01:57.970 --> 01:02:01.130
You picked out a peak that you're going to
go climb.

01:02:01.130 --> 01:02:03.150
You got your little espresso machine.

01:02:03.150 --> 01:02:05.520
You've gotten your laptop.

01:02:05.520 --> 01:02:08.240
You've gotten yourself, bought a lot of Patagonia
gear.

01:02:08.240 --> 01:02:09.240
We're thankful for that.

01:02:09.240 --> 01:02:10.840
You got yourself all dressed up.

01:02:10.840 --> 01:02:15.950
And then you fly to the Himalayas and your
guide and outfitter meets you and the sherpas

01:02:15.950 --> 01:02:19.480
carry all your stuff up to base camp so you
don't have to carry anything.

01:02:19.480 --> 01:02:23.321
And you get there and you get a little satellite
dish and you go online and you say to your

01:02:23.321 --> 01:02:28.470
wife and family, "I'm here it's going to be
the greatest adventure of my life."

01:02:28.470 --> 01:02:34.349
And the morning you're supposed to summit,
the guide wakes you up fixes your breakfast

01:02:34.349 --> 01:02:40.150
and then one ropes up in front of you and
one is behind you to get you up to the summit

01:02:40.150 --> 01:02:41.820
and get you back.

01:02:41.820 --> 01:02:46.369
And then you come back to base camp and you
write to your friends and family, 'I summited

01:02:46.369 --> 01:02:47.369
today.

01:02:47.369 --> 01:02:50.130
I have one of the great achievements of my
lifetime'."

01:02:50.130 --> 01:02:51.620
He looked out on the audience.

01:02:51.620 --> 01:02:56.920
"I don't know how else to tell you this except,
you're an asshole when you left and an asshole

01:02:56.920 --> 01:02:59.109
when you got back."

01:02:59.109 --> 01:03:02.849
[laughter] It went totally viral on the Internet.

01:03:02.849 --> 01:03:05.900
And he got a standing ovation from the room.

01:03:05.900 --> 01:03:07.030
So I saw it.

01:03:07.030 --> 01:03:09.650
We got to keep that perspective in there as
well.

01:03:09.650 --> 01:03:10.680
Thank you all very much.

01:03:10.680 --> 01:03:10.890
[Applause]

